title: Clinton Spotted Dining With Her 'SNL' Counterpart, Kate McKinnon
text:
Screengrab via NBC-SNL/Youtube BTW 
Though President Trump ’s comedic counterpart, Alec Baldwin , seems to be having the time of his life mocking him, former candidate Hillary Clinton had a good time with hers. That'd be Saturday Night Live star Kate McKinnon. Hillary Clinton and the woman who plays her on SNL, Kate McKinnon, had dinner yesterday in the theater district https://t.co/A5t26SUUkP pic.twitter.com/6RqD5XZGNl — Jennifer Epstein (@jeneps) February 17, 2017 
Clinton was seen dining and laughing with McKinnon Wednesday night, at Orso in New York City. One diner chanted "lock him up," inverting Trump's election jail call for Clinton. 
Following dinner, Clinton would check out Glenn Close starring in Sunset Boulevard . The former secretary of state received a very warm welcome from the audience and the onstage talent. — Logan Culwell-Block (@loganculwell) February 16, 2017 
Her reception, and admiration for the arts, was remarkably different from the jeering that Vice President Mike Pence got in his viewing of Hamilton shortly after the divisive Trump’s election. 
Here’s the post-election cold open from November, where McKinnon plays Clinton performing Leonard Cohen’s “Hallelujah.”
